M|rules|title: Suppress Expected Hydration Mismatches
M|rules|impact: LOW-MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids noisy hydration warnings for known differences
M|rules|tags: rendering, hydration, ssr, nextjs
M|rules|In SSR frameworks (e.g., Next.js), some values are intentionally different on server vs client (random IDs, dates, locale/timezone formatting). For these *expected* mismatches, wrap the dynamic text i
M|rules|**Incorrect (known mismatch warnings):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Timestamp() {
M|rules|return <span>{new Date().toLocaleString()}</span>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (suppress expected mismatch only):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Timestamp() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<span suppressHydrationWarning>
M|rules|{new Date().toLocaleString()}
M|rules|</span>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```